    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. So it's a bit of a divide between the 'technical' crowd and the 'mainstream' researchers. If a company were sitting on the fence, would it be more responsible to follow a precautionary approach and slow down until these theoretical risks are solved, or is the risk of falling behind in the global AI race actually a bigger danger to society?",
